class: a class is an template of any object
object: an object is an instanace of a class
instnace : physical stuff of the class which exist
           for real
           example : class humankind
                     object real human
                     real humans are instnace of the class
                     humankind
           class are blueprint/rules/logical construct not actual things
           object are physical reality occupies space in memory/ram

objecs are stored in the heap memory
ref variavle are stored in the stack memory

instnce variable are the variable that are declared inside
 the class

class Student{
        int rno;
        String name;
        float marks;
    }
    Student student1;  -> a ref var in call stack point to null
    heap memroy have the acutal object
    student1 = new Student();
    new operator : dyanamiclly (at run time) allocates memrory
    and reutrn a reference variable to it

    Student std1 = new Student();
    to the left of = happends during comple time and
    to te right of = happends during run time (dynamic)